+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QFhAgLdBDGjF7XNTcsNj15","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE STATIC SITE GENERATOR TOOLKIT EXPLORATION\n\n### 1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   └── core/\n│       ├── engine.ts       (BuildEngine class - plugin orchestration)\n│       ├── index.ts        (Exports)\n│       ├── types.ts        (All interfaces/types)\n│       └── templates.ts    (Default and List templates)\n│   └── plugins/            (EMPTY - contains only .gitkeep)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts        (15 core tests - MUST PASS)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       └── dev-server.test.ts\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── package.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n├── .eslintrc.cjs\n└── TASK.md\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. PLUGIN INTERFACE (src/core/types.ts)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;              // Plugin identifier\n  version: string;           // Semantic version\n  dependencies: string[];    // Names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;       // Hook implementations\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\n\n**Three Hook Types:**\n1. **beforeBuild** - Runs once before processing files (good for initialization)\n2. **transformContent** - Runs on each file individually in plugin order\n3. **afterBuild** - Runs once after all files processed (good for generating index files)\n\n**Supporting Interfaces:**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // HTML or Markdown (raw)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // path -> rendered HTML\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. BUILD ENGINE (src/core/engine.ts)\n\n**Key Mechanisms:**\n\n```typescript\nclass BuildEngine {\n  // Plugin management\n  registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin): void\n  registerTemplate(template: Template): void\n  getPlugins(): Plugin[]\n  getTemplates(): Map<string, Template>\n\n  // DAG topological sort with cycle detection\n  resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]\n    // Throws on circular dependency\n    // Throws on missing dependency\n\n  // Main build pipeline\n  async build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>\n}\n```\n\n**Build Pipeline Flow:**\n1. Create context with empty output/assets/data maps\n2. Resolve plugin order using topological sort\n3. Run `beforeBuild` hooks in order\n4. Run `transformContent` hooks in order on each file\n5. Render templates and populate `ctx.output`\n6. Run `afterBuild` hooks in order\n7. Return context\n\n**Templates:**\n- Files matched against their `template` property (default: 'default')\n- Template receives: `title`, `slug`, `date`, `tags`, `siteTitle`, `baseUrl`, all metadata\n- Output key: `${file.slug}.html`\n\n---\n\n### 4. CORE TEST COVERAGE (tests/core.test.ts - 15 tests)\n\nAll tests must continue to pass. Tests validate:\n1. Plugin registration\n2. Template registration\n3. Default template rendering\n4. List template rendering\n5. Raw content fallback (no template)\n6. beforeBuild hook execution\n7. transformContent hook execution\n8. afterBuild hook execution\n9. Dependency order resolution\n10. Circular dependency detection\n11. Missing dependency detection\n12. Multiple plugins transformContent in order\n13. Shared data store functionality\n14. File metadata retention\n15. Empty file list handling\n\n---\n\n### 5. PLUGIN TEST SPECIFICATIONS\n\n#### **Plugin 1: markdown-ext** (NO DEPENDENCIES)\n**File:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts` - 8 tests\n\n**Requirements:**\n- `createMarkdownExtPlugin()` factory function\n- Hook: `transformContent`\n- Converts Markdown to HTML (using `marked` library from dependencies)\n- **Footnotes Support:** `[^1]` syntax\n  - Inline: `text[^1]` → `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n  - Definition: `[^1]: Text` stored and rendered at bottom\n  - Section: `<section class=\"footnotes\"><ol><li id=\"fn-1\">Text</li>...`\n- **Admonition Containers:** `:::type ... :::` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-{type}\">`\n  - Types: note, warning, tip\n- Preserves existing HTML\n- Handles empty content\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 2: asset-pipeline** (NO DEPENDENCIES)\n**File:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts` - 9 tests\n\n**Requirements:**\n- `createAssetPipelinePlugin()` factory function\n- Hook: `transformContent`\n- Rewrites relative asset URLs (`./image.png` → `/assets/image.png`)\n  - Works for `src=\"...\"` in img tags\n  - Works for `href=\"...\"` in links\n- Leaves absolute URLs (`https://...`) unchanged\n- Does NOT reprocess `/assets/...` URLs\n- Generates manifest in `ctx.data.set('asset-manifest', { assets: string[] })`\n  - Collects all unique asset filenames\n  - Persists across multiple files\n  - Empty if no assets found\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 3: syntax-highlight** (NO DEPENDENCIES)\n**File:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts` - 9 tests\n\n**Requirements:**\n- `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()` factory function\n- Hook: `transformContent`\n- Targets `<pre><code class=\"language-{lang}\">` blocks only\n- Adds classes: `class=\"language-{lang} highlighted\"`\n- Adds attribute: `<pre data-language=\"{lang}\">`\n- Processes multiple code blocks per file\n- Does NOT modify inline `<code>` tags\n- Does NOT process blocks without language class\n- Preserves code block content exactly\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 4: taxonomy** (NO DEPENDENCIES)\n**File:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts` - 10 tests\n\n**Requirements:**\n- `createTaxonomyPlugin()` factory function\n- Hooks: `beforeBuild` and `afterBuild`\n- **beforeBuild:** Builds tag index\n  - Reads `file.tags` array from each file\n  - Normalizes tags to lowercase\n  - Stores: `ctx.data.set('taxonomy-tags', Map<tag, ContentFile[]>)`\n  - Handles files with no tags\n- **afterBuild:** Generates tag pages\n  - One HTML page per tag: `tags/{tag}.html`\n  - Page lists all files with that tag with title links\n  - Example output: `<ul><li><a href=\"/post-1.html\">First Post</a></li>...`\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 5: rss-feed** (DEPENDS: markdown-ext, taxonomy)\n**File:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts` - 8 tests\n\n**Requirements:**\n- `createRssFeedPlugin()` factory function\n- Hook: `afterBuild`\n- Generates `feed.xml` with RSS 2.0 structure\n- **Structure:**\n  ```xml\n  <?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n  <rss version=\"2.0\">\n    <channel>\n      <title>{config.title}</title>\n      <link>{config.baseUrl}</link>\n      <item>\n        <title>{file.title}</title>\n        <link>{config.baseUrl}/{file.slug}.html</link>\n        <description><![CDATA[{file.content}]]></description>\n        <pubDate>{file.date}</pubDate>\n        <category>{tag}</category>\n      </item>\n    </channel>\n  </rss>\n  ```\n- Content is HTML (not Markdown) - uses CDATA wrapper\n- Items sorted by date (newest first)\n- Categories from tags (reads `taxonomy-tags` from `ctx.data`)\n- Handles files without dates (omits `<pubDate>` tag)\n- All URLs use `config.baseUrl`\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 6: search-index** (DEPENDS: markdown-ext, syntax-highlight)\n**File:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts` - 8 tests\n\n**Requirements:**\n- `createSearchIndexPlugin()` factory function\n- Hook: `afterBuild`\n- Generates `search-index.json` with searchable content\n- **Format:**\n  ```json\n  [\n    {\n      \"slug\": \"post-1\",\n      \"title\": \"Post 1\",\n      \"content\": \"Plain text without HTML tags\",\n      \"tags\": [\"js\", \"web\"]\n    }\n  ]\n  ```\n- HTML tags stripped from content (plain text only)\n- Code blocks included in content\n- Tags included if present\n- Valid JSON array\n- Handles empty file list (empty array)\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 7: sitemap** (DEPENDS: taxonomy, rss-feed)\n**File:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts` - 8 tests\n\n**Requirements:**\n- `createSitemapPlugin()` factory function\n- Hook: `afterBuild`\n- Generates `sitemap.xml` with all discoverable URLs\n- **Structure:**\n  ```xml\n  <?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n  <urlset xmlns=\"http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9\">\n    <url>\n      <loc>{config.baseUrl}/path.html</loc>\n    </url>\n  </urlset>\n  ```\n- Includes all entries from `ctx.output` map (content pages)\n- Includes all tag pages from `taxonomy-tags` in `ctx.data`\n- Includes `feed.xml` if present in output\n- Uses `config.baseUrl` for all URLs\n- Valid XML structure\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 8: dev-server** (DEPENDS: asset-pipeline, search-index)\n**File:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts` - 7 tests\n\n**Requirements:**\n- `createDevServerPlugin()` factory function\n- Hook: `afterBuild`\n- Generates dev server configuration\n- **Config Structure:**\n  ```typescript\n  {\n    port: number;                           // Default: 3000\n    routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n    assetPaths: string[];                   // From asset-manifest\n    searchIndexPath: string;                // \"/search-index.json\" if exists\n  }\n  ```\n- Stores: `ctx.data.set('dev-server-config', config)`\n- Routes:\n  - Content pages: `{ path: \"/post-1.html\", handler: \"static\" }`\n  - Asset routes: `{ path: \"/assets/image.png\", handler: \"asset\" }` (from asset-manifest)\n- Gracefully handles missing asset-pipeline data (empty assetPaths)\n- Handles missing search-index.json (empty searchIndexPath)\n\n---\n\n### 6. PACKAGE.JSON\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-ssg-toolkit\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"main\": \"dist/core/index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/marked\": \"^5.0.2\",\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"marked\": \"^17.0.2\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.57.1\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.9\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Dependencies Available:**\n- `marked` - Markdown parsing and conversion\n- `@types/marked` - TypeScript types for marked\n- `express` and `@types/express` - (Only needed for dev-server, optional)\n\n---\n\n### 7. TSCONFIG.JSON\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"strict\": true,              // Full strict mode\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",          // Node16+ module resolution\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"declaration\": true,         // Generate .d.ts files\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Compilation Notes:**\n- Strict mode enabled - all types must be correct\n- Outputs to `dist/` directory\n- Generates type declarations\n- ES2022 target with Node16+ module resolution\n\n---\n\n### 8. TEMPLATES (src/core/templates.ts)\n\n**Default Template:**\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>${title} | ${siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <article>\n    <h1>${title}</h1>\n    ${date ? `<time>${date}</time>` : ''}\n    <div class=\"content\">${content}</div>\n  </article>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n**List Template:**\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <title>${title} | ${siteTitle}</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>${title}</h1>\n  <div class=\"list\">${content}</div>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. TEST EXECUTION\n\n**Command:** `npm test` (runs vitest)\n- Tests require 15 existing core tests + 60 new plugin tests = 75 total\n- Test timeout: 10 seconds per test\n- All tests use vitest globals (no import needed)\n\n**Build Command:** `npm run build`\n- Runs TypeScript compiler with strict mode\n- Outputs to `/workspace/dist/`\n\n**Lint Command:** `npm run lint`\n- ESLint with TypeScript support\n- Must be clean with no errors\n\n---\n\n### 10. EXECUTION ORDER & DEPENDENCIES\n\n**Dependency Graph:**\n\n```\nWave 1 (No dependencies):\n  ├── markdown-ext\n  ├── asset-pipeline\n  ├── syntax-highlight\n  └── taxonomy\n\nWave 2 (Depend on Wave 1):\n  ├── rss-feed        (requires: markdown-ext, taxonomy)\n  └── search-index    (requires: markdown-ext, syntax-highlight)\n\nWave 3 (Depend on Wave 2):\n  ├── sitemap         (requires: taxonomy, rss-feed)\n  └── dev-server      (requires: asset-pipeline, search-index)\n```\n\n**Plugin Order Resolution:**\n- Engine uses topological sort to validate and order plugins\n- Throws error on circular dependencies\n- Throws error on missing dependencies\n- All plugins in correct order execute their hooks\n\n---\n\n### 11. KEY DATA FLOW PATTERNS\n\n**Cross-Plugin Communication via ctx.data:**\n\n1. **asset-pipeline** sets: `asset-manifest: { assets: string[] }`\n2. **dev-server** reads from asset-manifest\n3. **taxonomy** sets: `taxonomy-tags: Map<string, ContentFile[]>`\n4. **rss-feed** reads from taxonomy-tags\n5. **sitemap** reads from taxonomy-tags\n6. **dev-server** sets: `dev-server-config: {...}`\n\n---\n\n## SUMMARY FOR IMPLEMENTATION\n\nYou need to create 8 plugin files in `/workspace/src/plugins/`:\n\n1. `markdown-ext.ts` - Markdown to HTML with footnotes & admonitions\n2. `asset-pipeline.ts` - URL rewriting & manifest generation\n3. `syntax-highlight.ts` - Code block annotation\n4. `taxonomy.ts` - Tag indexing & tag page generation\n5. `rss-feed.ts` - RSS 2.0 feed generation\n6. `search-index.ts` - Searchable JSON index\n7. `sitemap.ts` - XML sitemap generation\n8. `dev-server.ts` - Dev server configuration\n\nEach plugin must:\n- Export `createXxxPlugin()` factory function\n- Return a `Plugin` object with correct name, version, dependencies, and hooks\n- Use only `transformContent` (for Waves 1) or `beforeBuild`/`afterBuild` (for Waves 2-3)\n- Store/read data via `ctx.data` for cross-plugin communication\n- Handle edge cases (empty content, missing data, etc.)\n\nAll 15 existing core tests must pass, plus all 60 plugin tests."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa57cdf (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 36529\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 52130</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"24600852-ab96-4981-bae8-5332da115cd9","uuid":"da26be1b-baf9-4efe-b0ef-8190a902cfad","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Very thoroughly explore this Static Site Generator toolkit codebase. I need to understand:\n\n1. The full directory structure\n2. The Plugin interface from src/core/types.ts - every field and method\n3. The build engine in src/core/ - how plugins are loaded and invoked\n4. The templates in src/core/\n5. All existing tests in tests/core.test.ts\n6. ALL test files in tests/plugins/ - read every single one completely\n7. The package.json for dependencies and scripts\n8. The tsconfig.json for compilation settings\n\nRead every file completely. I need the full picture to implement 8 plugins.","agentId":"aa57cdf","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE STATIC SITE GENERATOR TOOLKIT EXPLORATION\n\n### 1. DIRECTORY STRUCTURE\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   └── core/\n│       ├── engine.ts       (BuildEngine class - plugin orchestration)\n│       ├── index.ts        (Exports)\n│       ├── types.ts        (All interfaces/types)\n│       └── templates.ts    (Default and List templates)\n│   └── plugins/            (EMPTY - contains only .gitkeep)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts        (15 core tests - MUST PASS)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       └── dev-server.test.ts\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── package.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n├── .eslintrc.cjs\n└── TASK.md\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. PLUGIN INTERFACE (src/core/types.ts)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;              // Plugin identifier\n  version: string;           // Semantic version\n  dependencies: string[];    // Names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;       // Hook implementations\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\n\n**Three Hook Types:**\n1. **beforeBuild** - Runs once before processing files (good for initialization)\n2. **transformContent** - Runs on each file individually in plugin order\n3. **afterBuild** - Runs once after all files processed (good for generating index files)\n\n**Supporting Interfaces:**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // HTML or Markdown (raw)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // path -> rendered HTML\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. BUILD ENGINE (src/core/engine.ts)\n\n**Key Mechanisms:**\n\n```typescript\nclass BuildEngine {\n  // Plugin management\n  registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin): void\n  registerTemplate(template: Template): void\n  getPlugins(): Plugin[]\n  getTemplates(): Map<string, Template>\n\n  // DAG topological sort with cycle detection\n  resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]\n    // Throws on circular dependency\n    // Throws on missing dependency\n\n  // Main build pipeline\n  async build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>\n}\n```\n\n**Build Pipeline Flow:**\n1. Create context with empty output/assets/data maps\n2. Resolve plugin order using topological sort\n3. Run `beforeBuild` hooks in order\n4. Run `transformContent` hooks in order on each file\n5. Render templates and populate `ctx.output`\n6. Run `afterBuild` hooks in order\n7. Return context\n\n**Templates:**\n- Files matched against their `template` property (default: 'default')\n- Template receives: `title`, `slug`, `date`, `tags`, `siteTitle`, `baseUrl`, all metadata\n- Output key: `${file.slug}.html`\n\n---\n\n### 4. CORE TEST COVERAGE (tests/core.test.ts - 15 tests)\n\nAll tests must continue to pass. Tests validate:\n1. Plugin registration\n2. Template registration\n3. Default template rendering\n4. List template rendering\n5. Raw content fallback (no template)\n6. beforeBuild hook execution\n7. transformContent hook execution\n8. afterBuild hook execution\n9. Dependency order resolution\n10. Circular dependency detection\n11. Missing dependency detection\n12. Multiple plugins transformContent in order\n13. Shared data store functionality\n14. File metadata retention\n15. Empty file list handling\n\n---\n\n### 5. PLUGIN TEST SPECIFICATIONS\n\n#### **Plugin 1: markdown-ext** (NO DEPENDENCIES)\n**File:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts` - 8 tests\n\n**Requirements:**\n- `createMarkdownExtPlugin()` factory function\n- Hook: `transformContent`\n- Converts Markdown to HTML (using `marked` library from dependencies)\n- **Footnotes Support:** `[^1]` syntax\n  - Inline: `text[^1]` → `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n  - Definition: `[^1]: Text` stored and rendered at bottom\n  - Section: `<section class=\"footnotes\"><ol><li id=\"fn-1\">Text</li>...`\n- **Admonition Containers:** `:::type ... :::` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-{type}\">`\n  - Types: note, warning, tip\n- Preserves existing HTML\n- Handles empty content\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 2: asset-pipeline** (NO DEPENDENCIES)\n**File:** `/workspace/tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts` - 9 tests\n\n**Requirements:**\n- `createAssetPipelinePlugin()` factory function\n- Hook: `transformContent`\n- Rewrites relative asset URLs (`./image.png` → `/assets/image.png`)\n  - Works for `src=\"...\"` in img tags\n  - Works for `href=\"...\"` in links\n- Leaves absolute URLs (`https://...`) unchanged\n- Does NOT reprocess `/assets/...` URLs\n- Generates manifest in `ctx.data.set('asset-manifest', { assets: string[] })`\n  - Collects all unique asset filenames\n  - Persists across multiple files\n  - Empty if no assets found\n\n---\n\n#### **Plugin 3: syntax-highlight** (NO DEPENDENCIES)\n